name: Pennsylvania
notes: Pennsylvania uses both O and 0 together. Numbers are 1/4 inch taller than letters (typographic note). Both characters are allowed and used. Source: OOS.txt compilation - requires verification with official DMV documentation. Both O and 0 used; numbers are ¼" taller than letters.

processing_metadata.description: Official Pennsylvania DMV processing rules and validation requirements

stacked_characters.position: INCLUDE 'PD' by WHEELCHAIR SYMBOL, INCLUDE 'FF' in SYMBOL, INCLUDE 'US'/'NG'/'EM' stacked codes on service plates
stacked_characters.notes: Stacked characters must be keyed (e.g., PA-00447US, PA-NG250, PA-PD4161A, PA-71067PD - include small PD by wheelchair, PA-EM0000, PA-FF0000 - FF in symbol must be keyed)
